Docker images
Docker container ls
Docker ps -a //running docker

Stop container

Docker stop container name  //you can get id by running docker container command
docker start <container name>
Docker rm <container name> //remove
Docker kill <container id> //kill docker container


Remove container

Docker container rm container name
Docker kill <container id>

Docker container prue // removed stopped container

Remove images

Docker image  rm  <image_id>  // image id can be get from docker images command


Creating image

docker build . -t spring-boot-mysql //need to run from project base dir


Run mysql inside docker

docker pull mysql

Docker run --name <image_name>   -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=<password>  -e MYSQL_DATABASE=<db_name>
-d mysql:<tag>  //ex:- tag is usually version name. latest can be used here

Connect to AWS free Unix instance

ssh -i C:\Users\prateemi\Downloads\prateek_key.pem ec2-user@ec2-13-59-189-112.us-east-2.compute.amazonaws.com